  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Media and Information Literacy a Tool for Critical Citizen&apos;s Engagement.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">One obstacle preventing people from critically engaging, asserting their rights and advancing their place in development is lack of access to information and knowledge, and crucially the critical information and media competencies to participate in the public debate, which impacts their lives. Sustainable development with its emphasis on peace, human development, and rights requires a diverse and participatory media and information environments. MIL is a powerful and sustainable means to do this. This action responds to the growing call from Member States to enable media and information literate societies when the world faces unprecedented challenges. The action addresses capacity building, policy articulation, evidence through research, resource development and networking.</narrative>
  </description>
